Resize¶

In [89]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
for i in range(3):
    new_im = transforms.Resize((100,100))(img[i])
    plt.subplot(1,3,i+1)
    plt.imshow(new_im)

RandomErasing¶

In [100]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
for i in range(3):
    plt.subplot(1,3,i+1)
    data_transform=transforms.Compose([
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        transforms.RandomErasing(),
        transforms.ToPILImage()
    ])
    new_im = data_transform(img[i])
    plt.imshow(new_im)

Normalize¶

Normalize

In [101]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
for i in range(3):
    plt.subplot(1,3,i+1)
    data_transform=transforms.Compose([
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        transforms.Normalize([0.485,0.456,0.406],[0.229,0.224,0.225]),
        transforms.ToPILImage()
    ])
    new_im = data_transform(img[i])
    plt.imshow(new_im)
